item.title: What i do when this happen?
item.dc:creator: @xx_matty_xx Justin Bieber
item.description:
@xx_matty_xx wrote:

[quote=“Pwnd, post:5, topic:526568”][quote author=xx matty xx link=topic=645312.msg4341010#msg4341010 date=1375165824]
No he doesn’t, that’s the login page for his router. It’s probably because the router doesn’t properly handle loopback connections, but possible that it works from outside the network.
[/quote]How is that a link to his router’s address?[/quote]

Shorty626:

It is most likely his ISP does not support looping back. Its quite common.

I had this problem with an old router and a lot of people have had the same issue, but always get told they’re just being a noob and don’t know how to portforward. When you go to your public IP (or a hostname that points to your public IP), it will direct you to the routers page.
